The paper deals with learning the graphical structure of Bayesian Belief Networks (BBNs) from databases, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of incomplete databases is a challenge in data management (cs.DB) and the method proposed in the paper is deterministic, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
